feat: add seed category, click-to-home header, and category-chip toggle

Three connected UX requests landed together:

1. Seed as a 9th category
   - New "seed" arm of the Category union, default tan #C8A37B color, and
     a sunflower emoji as the per-card fallback.
   - QID Q40763 ("seed") in src/data/category-qids.json. The dedupe pass
     keeps almond / peanut / amaranth grain assigned to their existing
     categories (nut / legume / grain) since seed runs last; what remains
     is genuinely seed-only items: sunflower, sesame, chia, flax, poppy,
     pumpkin seed, hemp seed, etc.
   - Nine curated entries: sunflower / sesame / chia / flax / pumpkin /
     poppy / hemp / watermelon / lotus seed.
   - Snapshot regenerates to 1,867 items (up from 1,719). Cache key bumps
     to v6 so users with a v5 cache pick up the new category.

2. Header logo goes home
   - The Leaf icon + "The Produce Gallery" wordmark is now a button. A
     click resets filters, search query, sort, page, and the open detail
     modal, then smooth-scrolls to the top. Persistent preferences
     (theme, source) intentionally survive so the user lands back on the
     gallery the way they like to use it, not a factory-reset version.

3. Category chips toggle off
   - Clicking an already-active non-"All" category chip now clears the
     filter back to "All", matching the toggle behaviour the color chips
     and the has-photo button already had. Adds aria-pressed and a title
     attribute so the toggle is discoverable on hover and to screen
     readers.

Tests: two new Playwright cases in tests/smoke.spec.ts cover the toggle
and the home-click; both run as part of the regular smoke suite. README
is updated with the 9th category, corrected QIDs, the new ~1,870-item
snapshot, and v6 cache key.
